{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is the-- the border city between Austria and-- and Hungary.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was towards the end of the war, when when the transport line, the trail-- the-- the trains didn't function any longer.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Either it was bombed, and so on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So in their desperation then, to get the people deported, the Nazis-- that was the-- the Hungarian Nazis, who were active then, at that time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had taken over, you know, as I told you, at the end, towards the end, after the 15th of October.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They pushed the people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They took the people, as they were, standing in their ordinary clothes, perhaps in the streets or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They just took them all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Took them out from houses and pushed them to march these 200 kilometers in the snow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It took a week, that march to-- to the border.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Where then they were taken over by-- by the German Eichmann commando and sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But that was a very barbaric way of doing it, because they-- they had to spend the night in open air, in the cold.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- and there were corpses all around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were dying during the way, during the march, and all that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And what we could do was very little.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We tried to distribute food and all that as-- as much as we could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was forbidden, of course.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And Wallenberg managed, at the border town there, to save a few people also.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Now and then, there are many of these episodes which I was a-- where I was a witness.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had-- we had one car, together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we had trucks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and when Wallenberg managed to-- he bribed them, these Nazi people there and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
